In England, in the seven days to 14 September, there were 149,844 new confirmed cases (265.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 07 September, there were 194,433 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 23% (44,589 fewer cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 19 September is 6,347,616 (11,224.8 cases per 100,000 population).
